===Alternative forms===
* {{l|de|des Abends}} {{q|dated}}

===Etymology===
From {{inh|de|gmh|ābendes}}, adverbial genitive of {{m|gmh|ābent}}, whence modern {{cog|de|Abend||evening}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|de|/ˈaːbən(t)s/}}
* {{audio|de|De-at-abends.ogg|Audio (Austria)}}

===Adverb===
{{head|de|adverb}}

# in the [[evening]], in the [[early]] [[night]]; note that evening and night are considered separate times of day and that "Abend" lasts into the night hours, generally until bed time or up to midnight.
#* ''[[von]] [[morgens]] [[bis]] '''abends'''''
#*: from morning to night
# [[p.m.]], used to indicate that a given 12-hour time is in the evening; German has no direct equivalent for a.m./p.m. but uses the appropriate time of day instead.
#* ''8 Uhr '''abends'''''
#*: 8 p.m.

